6:
Melsele! Where are you? 
Answer me! Melsele!
8:
The Resistance members are gone 
too... But how does a force that big just 
disappear?
19:
Looks like the fiends sent me a few 
playmates.
21:
It's quiet... Far too quiet for 
a battlefield.
38:
What did you do to me?! Are you 
working with the fiends?!
45:
Welcome to Starview Village. I am its 
Keeper, Stella.
49: Starview Village? I can't believe it...
54:
That’s one of the Stars Immemorial... 
El Zand.
59:
My name is Eleanor. I'm an elf, one of 
the Beings who Wake Beneath the 
Stars.
I'm sorry I pointed my sword at you.
62:
You were caught unawares in the heat 
of battle. Anyone would have done the 
same.
...But you're an elf, you say?
70:
Only what I have heard from myths 
and children's tales. I did not think 
them real.
75:
My people have existed since ancient 
times. We are growers of trees, writers 
of songs, and when need calls for it, 
soldiers of war.
77:
Currently, we and a group of humans 
are working together to bring down 
the fiends.
81:
What sort of creatures are these 
fiends?
85:
They have blue skin, red wings, and 
curved horns. But most of the time 
we're stuck fighting their pets—
sickening beasts called daemons.
89: Then they are the same fiends I know.
91:
It's as I thought. Ours is not the only 
realm they have invaded.
96:
...So the Stars Immemorial are other 
worlds.
98:
It's said that stars have gotten dimmer 
and smaller with time.
100:
Only through the Stars Immemorial 
can we glimpse their formal glory.
...I've heard about El Zand in the songs 
of the high elves.
103:
They also sang of Starview Village... 
But I never thought I'd find it on 
another world.
108: Stella, what do you know of the elves?
125:
Eleanor. We find ourselves in similar 
circumstances.
128:
I too seek a way home, so I may bring 
the Dark Throne to justice.
Will you not join us?
134:
Bring the Dark Throne to justice? 
...But you're tiny.
137:
...Sorry. I was just surprised by your 
courage.
139: It would be an honor to join you.
149:
We're glad to have you with us, 
Eleanor.
154:
Stay safe, Melsele... I'll find my way 
back to you, I promise.
